ml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"event marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"event tickets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"WooCommerce\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1567725\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:622:\"<p>WooCommerce is one of the most popular e-commerce platforms in the world. And while the core plugin provides stellar functionality, you can add even more oomph to your site by enhancing it with extensions and add-ons. Out of more than 290 official extensions in their library, we’ve narrowed down the top four to help event&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/awesome-woocommerce-extensions-for-event-ticket-sales/\">Awesome WooCommerce Extensions for Event Ticket Sales</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"George\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4525:\"<p>WooCommerce is one of the most popular e-commerce platforms in the world. And while the core plugin provides stellar functionality, you can add even more oomph to your site by enhancing it with extensions and add-ons.</p>\n<p>Out of more than <a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/product-category/woocommerce-extensions/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">290 official extensions in their library</a>, we’ve narrowed down the top four to help event organizers boost ticket sales.</p>\n<h2>Name Your Price</h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/products/name-your-price/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Name Your Price extension</a> lets you structure ticket prices so attendees can “pay what you can.” This WooCommerce extension is particularly popular among nonprofits, religious organizations, and community groups. It’s a great way to cast a wide net and empower folks from all walks of life to chip in what they can, without having to worry about missing out an event.</p>\n<h2>Memberships</h2>\n<p>Each ticket sold to an attendee is typically a one-time sale. With <a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/products/woocommerce-memberships/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WooCommerce Memberships</a>, you can create a membership system that opens up a new stream of recurring revenue for your business or organization.</p>\n<p>While increasing or establishing recurring revenue is great, memberships have additional value beyond the bottom line. Venues of all types—from museums and gyms to community theaters and conference spaces—often sell memberships as a way to increase engagement and encourage the growth of a community around the venue.</p>\n<h2>Deposits</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/products/woocommerce-deposits/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WooCommerce Deposits</a> is an extension that lets you collect down payments and set up payment plans for event tickets or other products on your site. By making a high-price ticket financially accessible to more attendees, <strong>you can dramatically increase your ticket sales and conversion rates.</strong></p>\n<p>The website of <a href=\"https://colinprior.co.uk/workshops/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">photographer Colin Prior</a> is a great example of this extension in action. People rave about the week-long guided photojournalism retreats he offers through his website (using The Events Calendar, no less!), and they sell out quickly whenever a new set of dates is announced. The retreats themselves are quite expensive, but <strong>WooCommerce Deposits makes tickets easier to purchase </strong>by letting folks make an initial down payment to reserve their spot and pay the rest of the balance over time.</p>\n<h2>Product Bundles</h2>\n<p>Bundling products together is a great way to boost sales and the popular, beloved <a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/products/product-bundles/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Product Bundles extension</a> (it’s got an average rating of five stars!) helps you achieve just that.</p>\n<p>One of the most common uses for this extension is bundling physical merchandise with ticket sales. If you’re selling tickets to a workshop, for example, you may have a workbook or other learning materials attendees will need. Likewise with tickets to a concert—with bundles, you can offer a discounted album or piece of band merchandise along with tickets to the show.</p>\n<h2>Selling the Tickets Themselves</h2>\n<p>When we built our free and premium event ticketing solutions, one of the early design choices we made was making sure &#8220;tickets&#8221; are variants of the WooCommerce &#8220;Product&#8221; post type. Because of this, <strong>our plugins play nice with most WooCommerce extensions out-of-the-box.</strong></p>\n<p>We&#8217;re stoked that <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-event-tickets\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Event Tickets</a> and <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-event-tickets-plus/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Event Tickets Plus</a> both work well with each of the extensions mentioned here, and regardless of what ticketing platform you use, we hope some (or all) of these extensions help take your events and ticket sales to the next level.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/awesome-woocommerce-extensions-for-event-ticket-sales/\">Awesome WooCommerce Extensions for Event Ticket Sales</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"Classic Blocks: Going Gutenberg Chapter 6\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/classic-blocks-gutenberg/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 18 Jul 2018 01:35:09 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Articles\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Going Gutenberg\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Gutenberg\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1569481\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:626:\"<p>One of the biggest concerns about Gutenberg is how its arrival will affect WordPress sites’ preexisting content. Watching the Gutenberg team think through this problem and implement robust backwards compatibility has been both interesting and comforting. As we thought about our 600,000+ users of The Events Calendar, and what the process of transitioning to Gutenberg&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/classic-blocks-gutenberg/\">Classic Blocks: Going Gutenberg Chapter 6</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"George\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13552:\"<p>One of the biggest concerns about Gutenberg is how its arrival will affect WordPress sites’ preexisting content. Watching the Gutenberg team think through this problem and implement <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/core/2017/01/17/editor-technical-overview/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">robust backwards compatibility</a> has been both interesting and comforting.</p>\n<p>As we thought about our 600,000+ users of The Events Calendar, and what the process of transitioning to Gutenberg would be like for them, we wondered if there was anything more we could do to ensure the block editor would play nicely with preexisting event content on their sites. Thanks to the underlying work of the Gutenberg team, the data would be there, but it would now be broken up into separate blocks.</p>\n<p>We asked ourselves—<strong>would users find that confusing? And if so, how could we quell the fears about lost data</strong> and make it clear that their calendars and events hadn’t been negatively affected by the new editor?</p>\n<h2>Mere Survival of Data is Not Enough</h2>\n<p>In the classic editor, an event’s title and description have their own fields. <em>Everything else</em> is in one primary meta box. By contrast, when you create an event in the new block editor you have <em>separate blocks for <strong>each</strong></em> of the following event details:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Event Title</li>\n<li>Event Date Time</li>\n<li>Event Featured Image</li>\n<li>Event Price</li>\n<li>Event Organizer</li>\n<li>Event Location (Venue)</li>\n<li>Event Website</li>\n<li>Event Sharing</li>\n</ul>\n<div id=\"attachment_1569498\" style=\"width: 1167px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"http://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/image1-1.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1569498\" src=\"http://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/image1-1.png\" alt=\"A New Event in the Block Editor\" width=\"1157\" height=\"1090\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/image1-1.png 1157w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/image1-1-90x85.png 90w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/image1-1-300x283.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/image1-1-768x724.png 768w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/image1-1-665x626.png 665w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/image1-1-430x405.png 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/image1-1-645x608.png 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/image1-1-1068x1006.png 1068w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/image1-1-460x433.png 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/image1-1-600x565.png 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/image1-1-500x471.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1157px) 100vw, 1157px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">The default blocks shown to a user when creating a new event in the block editor.</p></div>\n<p><strong>The problem when activating the block editor for the first time is this:</strong> The preexisting data from The Events Calendar <em>survives</em>, <strong>but it looks quite different</strong>. So different that it could easily be disorienting for users, and could give the impression that event data had been lost—even though it hadn’t.</p>\n<h2>Our Solution: The Classic Block</h2>\n<p>To bridge the gap between the classic editor (where most event data is in one meta box) and the new block editor (where most pieces of event data have their own block), we decided to create a &#8220;classic block&#8221;.</p>\n<p>The aptly-named &#8220;Event Details Classic&#8221; block is basically a 1:1 recreation of the original “event details” meta box that all pre-Gutenberg users of The Events Calendar will be familiar with.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_1574958\" style=\"width: 1357px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"http://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1574958\" src=\"http://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox.png\" alt=\"The Original Event Details Metabox\" width=\"1347\" height=\"1451\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox.png 1347w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox-79x85.png 79w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox-278x300.png 278w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox-768x827.png 768w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox-665x716.png 665w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox-430x463.png 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox-645x695.png 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox-1068x1150.png 1068w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox-460x496.png 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox-300x323.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox-600x646.png 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-original-metagox-500x539.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1347px) 100vw, 1347px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">The original Event Details metabox</p></div>\n<div id=\"attachment_1574952\" style=\"width: 2018px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"http://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-event-details-classic.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1574952\" src=\"http://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-event-details-classic.png\" alt=\"Event Details Classic Block\" width=\"2008\" height=\"1240\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-event-details-classic.png 2008w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-event-details-classic-138x85.png 138w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-event-details-classic-300x185.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-event-details-classic-768x474.png 768w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-event-details-classic-665x411.png 665w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-event-details-classic-430x266.png 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-event-details-classic-645x398.png 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-event-details-classic-1068x660.png 1068w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-event-details-classic-460x284.png 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-event-details-classic-600x371.png 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/07/guten6-event-details-classic-500x309.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2008px) 100vw, 2008px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">The Event Details Classic Block on an event.</p></div>\n<p>This provides easy access to and higher visibility of some of the most essential pieces of event data. Plus, this keeps them in a more familiar data structure than having each part in its own disconnected block.</p>\n<h2>How Long Will This Solution Last?</h2>\n<p>The Gutenberg team has made clear that they’ll support meta boxes and the classic editor <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/gutenberg/handbook/reference/faq/#given-gutenberg-is-built-in-javascript-how-will-old-meta-boxes-php-work\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">for the long-foreseeable future</a>. <strong>As long as they support both things, so will we.</strong> We’ll also continue to improve our &#8220;classic block&#8221; philosophy as needed, possibly creating more classic blocks as we integrate other The Events Calendar add-ons with the block editor.</p>\n<hr style=\"width: 70%; margin-left: 15%; margin-right: 15%;\" />\n<p>The work of the Gutenberg team will ensure preexisting data from the classic editor on any given site remains <em>intact</em>. The importance of this cannot be understated, but for us, it’s still not <em>quite enough</em>—we want to ensure that content not only persists, but <strong>looks good and is can preserved in as close to its original form as possible.</strong></p>\n<p>Our hope is that by having a good experience with the transition to the new block editor, users of <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">The Events Calendar</a> will feel comfortable experimenting with blocks and seeing just how much the new editor has to offer for old and new content alike.</p>\n<hr style=\"width: 30%; margin-left: 35%; margin-right: 35%;\" />\n<p><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.4/72x72/1f514.png\" alt=\"🔔\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> <strong>Please Note:</strong> This is a blog series about active development and exploration. Anything we mention here is subject to change, and this blog series should be read as a tentative roadmap for our products—not an official release plan.</p>\n<hr style=\"width: 30%; margin-left: 35%; margin-right: 35%;\" />\n<p>Want more Gutenberg news? Sign up for our Block Editor updates.</p>\n\n                <div class=\'gf_browser_unknown gform_wrapper\' id=\'gform_wrapper_28\' ><form method=\'post\' enctype=\'multipart/form-data\'  id=\'gform_28\'  action=\'/feed/\'>\n                        <div class=\'gform_body\'><ul id=\'gform_fields_28\' class=\'gform_fields top_label form_sublabel_below description_below\'><li id=\'field_28_1\'  class=\'gfield gfield_contains_required field_sublabel_below field_description_below gfield_visibility_visible\' ><label class=\'gfield_label\' for=\'input_28_1\' >Name<span class=\'gfield_required\'>*</span></label><div class=\'ginput_container ginput_container_text\'><input name=\'input_1\' id=\'input_28_1\' type=\'text\' value=\'\' class=\'medium\'     aria-required=\"true\" aria-invalid=\"false\" /></div></li><li id=\'field_28_2\'  class=\'gfield gfield_contains_required field_sublabel_below field_description_below gfield_visibility_visible\' ><label class=\'gfield_label\' for=\'input_28_2\' >Email Address<span class=\'gfield_required\'>*</span></label><div class=\'ginput_container ginput_container_text\'><input name=\'input_2\' id=\'input_28_2\' type=\'text\' value=\'\' class=\'medium\'     aria-required=\"true\" aria-invalid=\"false\" /></div></li>\n                            </ul></div>\n        <div class=\'gform_footer top_label\'> <input type=\'submit\' id=\'gform_submit_button_28\' clas